<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Sybil Smith</strong></span> is a writer and nurse who lives on the Vermont side of the Connecticut River. Since she wrote the essay in this issue, she has made contact with the divine. Much to her surprise, God turned out to be a talking otter. They are presently meeting on the river at sundown, so that God can explain her reasons for having set up the world the way she did.</p><a href="/contributors/sybil-smith" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

